cubes.name: semantic_catalog
cubes.title: Semantic Catalog
cubes.description: This a metadata about semantic views. This catalog share the complete information of all the semantic views available to a user along with other meta data like Semantic Catalog, Dimension Name, Attribute Type, Dimension Title, SQL Expression, Is it Primary Key, Dimension Data Type, Table Name, Cube Description, Cube Title, Cube Data Source, Semantic View Name,  Semantic View Title, Semantic View Description, Visible in Semantic View, Relationship Path, Semantic View Folder Name.

dimensions.name: semantic_catalog.dimension_name
dimensions.title: Semantic Catalog Dimension Name
dimensions.description: Technical Name of a dimension in a Cube.dev semantic tool

dimensions.name: semantic_catalog.dimension_measure_flag
dimensions.title: Semantic Catalog Attribute Type
dimensions.description: Type of an attribute in a semantic view, it could be a dimension or a measure

dimensions.name: semantic_catalog.dimension_title
dimensions.title: Semantic Catalog Dimension Title
dimensions.description: It is label or name provided by Business User

dimensions.name: semantic_catalog.dimension_sql
dimensions.title: Semantic Catalog SQL Expression
dimensions.description: It is an expression or a databse column from a table.

dimensions.name: semantic_catalog.primary_key
dimensions.title: Semantic Catalog Is it Primary Key
dimensions.description: It identifies if it used as a primary key of table.

dimensions.name: semantic_catalog.dimension_type
dimensions.title: Semantic Catalog Dimension Data Type
dimensions.description: It is data type of dimensional value. It is could be a string, number, datetime or a geo spatial cordinate

dimensions.name: semantic_catalog.cube_sql_table
dimensions.title: Semantic Catalog Table Name
dimensions.description: It is name of the database table/view or name of could be a derived sql in cube.dev

dimensions.name: semantic_catalog.cube_description
dimensions.title: Semantic Catalog Cube Description
dimensions.description: It is description about a cube that contributes towards a semantic view in cube.dev

dimensions.name: semantic_catalog.cube_title
dimensions.title: Semantic Catalog Cube Title
dimensions.description: It is label or name provided by Business User to a cube in cube.dev

dimensions.name: semantic_catalog.cube_data_source
dimensions.title: Semantic Catalog Cube Data Source
dimensions.description: It is label or name provided data source in cube.dev. For e.g. Breeding data sources, Veg data sources.

dimensions.name: semantic_catalog.view_name
dimensions.title: Semantic Catalog Semantic View Name
dimensions.description: Technical Name of a semantic view in a Cube.dev semantic tool

dimensions.name: semantic_catalog.view_title
dimensions.title: Semantic Catalog Semantic View Title
dimensions.description: It is label or name given to Semantic View Name to map to Business Context. It is provided by Business Users

dimensions.name: semantic_catalog.view_description
dimensions.title: Semantic Catalog Semantic View Description
dimensions.description: It is description about a Semantic View Name to map to Business Context. It is provided by Business Users

dimensions.name: semantic_catalog.visible_in_view
dimensions.title: Semantic Catalog Visible in Semantic View
dimensions.description: It is flag that indicates if a dimension is enables to access through any Semantic View

dimensions.name: semantic_catalog.join_path
dimensions.title: Semantic Catalog Relationship Path
dimensions.description: It show how different cubes(tables) in cube.dev connect in a Semantic View

dimensions.name: semantic_catalog.join_sql
dimensions.title: Semantic Catalog Relationship SQL
dimensions.description: It is the join condition in cube.dev

dimensions.name: semantic_catalog.join_relationship
dimensions.title: Semantic Catalog Relationship Cardinalities
dimensions.description: It show the cardinality between cubes. For e.g. one_to_one, one_to_many, many_to_one, many_to_many

dimensions.name: semantic_catalog.view_folder_name
dimensions.title: Semantic Catalog Semantic View Folder Name
dimensions.description: It is the name of the business entitiy used to organize the dimensions/measures in a Semantic View

dimensions.name: semantic_catalog.adapt_environment
dimensions.title: Semantic Catalog ADAPT Environment
dimensions.description: This shows the ADAPT Environment associated to the Semantic Catalog

dimensions.name: semantic_catalog.adapt_environment_url
dimensions.title: Semantic Catalog ADAPT URL
dimensions.description: This shows the ADAPT Environment URL associated to the Semantic Catalog

cubes.name: edited_allele_analysis
cubes.title: Edited Allele Analysis
cubes.description: A combined view of EditedAlleleCallID, EditedAlleleID, and SMEv2SEQProject_meta_data to provide a unified dataset for allele analysis and sequencing project metadata.

measures.name: edited_allele_analysis.count_distinct_edited_allele_call_id
measures.title: Edited Allele Analysis Distinct Count of Edited Allele Call ID
measures.description: This is to get Distinct count of Edited Allele Call ID
measures.shortTitle: Distinct Count of Edited Allele Call ID

measures.name: edited_allele_analysis.sum_of_allele_call_read_count
measures.title: Edited Allele Analysis Total Allele Call Reads
measures.description: This is to get sum of Allele Call Read Counts

measures.name: edited_allele_analysis.count_distinct_seqlims_project
measures.title: Edited Allele Analysis Distinct Count of Sequence Project
measures.description: This is to get distinct count of Sequence Project

measures.name: edited_allele_analysis.count_distinct_edited_allele_id
measures.title: Edited Allele Analysis Distinct Count of Edited Allele ID
measures.description: This is to get Distinct count of Edited Allele ID
measures.shortTitle: Distinct Count of Edited Allele ID

dimensions.name: edited_allele_analysis.edited_allele_call_id
dimensions.title: Edited Allele Analysis Edited Allele Call ID
dimensions.description: A concatenation of Sample ID Product 360 (p360) curated reference assembly including the chromosome or contig pollux ID identifying the guide used coordinate of the guide on the reference assembly and local_CIGAR. This makes this effectively a UUID for SME2.

dimensions.name: edited_allele_analysis.sample_id
dimensions.title: Edited Allele Analysis Sample ID
dimensions.description: The Sample ID as designated by the LIMS system note is a concatenation of underscore separated SEQID and sample number.

dimensions.name: edited_allele_analysis.call_ref_id
dimensions.title: Edited Allele Analysis Reference ID
dimensions.description: The Bayer Product 360 curated reference assembly including the chromosome (contig) the allele is on.

dimensions.name: edited_allele_analysis.barcode
dimensions.title: Edited Allele Analysis Barcode
dimensions.description: Barcode refers to the plant barcode or gds barcode as provided from LIMS and importantly is sample specific.

dimensions.name: edited_allele_analysis.reagent
dimensions.title: Edited Allele Analysis Reagent
dimensions.description: This generally refers to constructs or pMONs but in the future could indicate other methodologies for introducing foreign DNA.

dimensions.name: edited_allele_analysis.guide_name
dimensions.title: Edited Allele Analysis Guide Name
dimensions.description: Pollux ID from SeqUR for the guide used to create this edit.

dimensions.name: edited_allele_analysis.allele_call_read_count
dimensions.title: Edited Allele Analysis Allele Call Read Counts
dimensions.description: Count of reads with this allele call covering the guide window.

dimensions.name: edited_allele_analysis.percent_of_reads_covering_guide
dimensions.title: Edited Allele Analysis Percent Reads
dimensions.description: Percentage of reads covering the guide with this exact allele. Calculated as allele_call_read_count over total_reads_covering_guide.

dimensions.name: edited_allele_analysis.hamming_distance
dimensions.title: Edited Allele Analysis Hamming Distance
dimensions.description: Number of differences between two sequences of the same length in this case the reference sequence and aligned read sequence.

dimensions.name: edited_allele_analysis.allele_call_date_time
dimensions.title: Edited Allele Analysis Allele Call Uploaded Datetime
dimensions.description: A timestamp of when this record was uploaded for discriminating between updates - usually due to reruns.

dimensions.name: edited_allele_analysis.seqlims_project
dimensions.title: Edited Allele Analysis Sequence Project
dimensions.description: SEQID is the discrete unit of projects that go through the sequencing lab and groups a set of samples that were sequenced together in a library.

dimensions.name: edited_allele_analysis.sequencing_run
dimensions.title: Edited Allele Analysis Sequence Run ID
dimensions.description: The run identifier from the sequencer that this project was ran on for backtracking and unifying with sequencing QC.

dimensions.name: edited_allele_analysis.number_of_samples_included
dimensions.title: Edited Allele Analysis Samples Included
dimensions.description: The number of samples that were above the minimum required threshold (and met QC criteria) for inclusion in analysis.

dimensions.name: edited_allele_analysis.number_of_samples_excluded
dimensions.title: Edited Allele Analysis Samples Excluded
dimensions.description: The number of samples that were not above the minimum required threshold (or did not meet other QC criteria) for inclusion in analysis.

dimensions.name: edited_allele_analysis.analysis_cutoff_used
dimensions.title: Edited Allele Analysis Analysis Cutoff Used
dimensions.description: A float used to cutoff the analysis and keep noise due to sequencing error out of the results.

dimensions.name: edited_allele_analysis.min_reads_used
dimensions.title: Edited Allele Analysis Min Reads Used
dimensions.description: The minimum number of reads that must be present for a sample to be retained in the results otherwise filtered out.

dimensions.name: edited_allele_analysis.sequencing_project_date_time
dimensions.title: Edited Allele Analysis Sequence Project Uploaded Datetime
dimensions.description: A timestamp of when this record was uploaded for discriminating between updates - usually due to reruns.

dimensions.name: edited_allele_analysis.edited_allele_id
dimensions.title: Edited Allele Analysis Edited Allele ID
dimensions.description: A concatenation of reference name identifier with chromosome (contig) 5' coordinate start of guide and local CIGAR.

dimensions.name: edited_allele_analysis.allele_type
dimensions.title: Edited Allele Analysis Allele Type
dimensions.description: Type of allele, one of 'edit', 'wt', or 'offsite'.

dimensions.name: edited_allele_analysis.edited_allele_ref_id
dimensions.title: Edited Allele Analysis Reference ID
dimensions.description: The Bayer Product 360 curated reference assembly including the chromosome (contig) the allele is on.

dimensions.name: edited_allele_analysis.fp_sequence
dimensions.title: Edited Allele Analysis Five Prime Sequence
dimensions.description: Five prime sequence which is the sequence upstream of the guide window not including gaps.

dimensions.name: edited_allele_analysis.tp_sequence
dimensions.title: Edited Allele Analysis Three Prime Sequence
dimensions.description: Three prime sequence which is the sequence downstream of the guide window not including gaps.

dimensions.name: edited_allele_analysis.ref_string
dimensions.title: Edited Allele Analysis Reference string
dimensions.description: The wild-type or reference sequence of the guide region.

dimensions.name: edited_allele_analysis.match_string
dimensions.title: Edited Allele Analysis Sequence Match string
dimensions.description: The sequence of the read aligned segment for the allele.

dimensions.name: edited_allele_analysis.CIGAR
dimensions.title: Edited Allele Analysis CIGAR(Compact Idiosyncratic Gapped Alignment Report)
dimensions.description: Compact idiosyncratic gapped alignment report for the entire read with respect to the edited allele.

dimensions.name: edited_allele_analysis.allele_date_time
dimensions.title: Edited Allele Analysis Allele Uploaded Datetime
dimensions.description: A timestamp of when this record was uploaded for discriminating between updates - usually due to reruns.

dimensions.name: edited_allele_analysis.local_CIGAR
dimensions.title: Edited Allele Analysis Local CIGAR(Compact Idiosyncratic Gapped Alignment Report)
dimensions.description: The CIGAR localized to the guide region including notation for contiguous edits outside the guide window.
dimensions.shortTitle: Local CIGAR(Compact Idiosyncratic Gapped Alignment Report)
